INSERT INTO public.apisourcedocuments (id, createdat, secondarykey, updatedat, apisource, description, ingestedat, lastcheck, lat, location, lon, text) VALUES (368071977971712, '2026-06-19 15:05:40.161153', 295514619002880, NULL, 'rssFeeds', 'Rss items from Deutsche Welle', '2026-03-06 15:52:57.775456', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This document is a recolections of Rss items from Deutsche Welle

Title: US-Iran deal: Tehran says Israel withdrawal from Lebanon key
Publication date: 2026-06-16T10:00:00Z
Description: Iran’s top diplomat says any continued Israeli presence in Lebanon would violate the interim U.S.–Iran deal to end the war. Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu insists Israel will remain as long as necessary. DW has more.

Title: Pakistan raises defense spending amid regional conflicts
Publication date: 2026-06-16T13:00:00Z
Description: The sharp defense spending hike highlights lessons Pakistan has learned from recent conflicts with India and a growing focus on new warfare technologies, regardless of economic constraints imposed by the IMF.

Title: Sigh of relief in Africa as the Strait of Hormuz ''reopens''
Publication date: 2026-06-16T10:25:00Z
Description: A potential US-Iran agreement could lower energy, fertilizer, and food prices in Africa if the Strait of Hormuz fully reopens. Oil exporters such as Nigeria and Angola might have to cope with less revenue, experts say.

Title: Germany: 25 years of compensating Nazi-era forced laborers
Publication date: 2026-06-16T13:31:00Z
Description: A German fund established to compensate the millions forced to work for the Nazi regime has marked 25 years since the first payments were made. But for many it was much too late.

Title: NATO chief focuses on alliance unity after US alters pledges
Publication date: 2026-06-17T12:00:00Z
Description: NATO''s secretary general went to great lengths to cast a positive light on the alliance ahead of a ministers'' meeting. The closest he came to addressing any tension was saying members have "a lot to talk about."

Title: Germany World Cup shirts run out of letter V
Publication date: 2026-06-17T11:04:00Z
Description: Bad news for fans of Germany players Kai Havertz, Deniz Undav and Aleksandar Pavlovic: the kit makers have run out of the letter V, such is the demand for those names on shirts. But don''t worry, more Vs are on the way!

Title: Ebola and the US patient spotlight global health ''injustice''
Publication date: 2026-06-17T10:34:00Z
Description: The story of the US doctor who survived Ebola with experimental treatment in Germany highlights wider inequities in global health. It also reveals how sharply medical standards can differ between African countries.

Title: South Korea to shrink security buffer zone to North Korea
Publication date: 2026-06-17T10:23:00Z
Description: South Korea will ease restrictions on roughly 270 square kilometers of land near the border with North Korea. Farmers in the area had long complained of rules that complicated working conditions.

Title: India: Telegram to challenge government order blocking app
Publication date: 2026-06-17T09:56:00Z
Description: Telegram has reportedly challenged the Indian government''s order to temporarily block the popular messaging app ahead of the NEET medical entrance exam.

Title: Germany news: Ministers discuss refugee deportation rules
Publication date: 2026-06-17T09:52:00Z
Description: Germany''s regional interior ministers are holding their biannual conference with immigration, deportations and benefits high on the agenda. Meanwhile, Germany and Poland are marking 35 years of cooperation. DW has more.

Title: Is Russia heading for a fuel crisis?
Publication date: 2026-06-17T09:28:00Z
Description: Russia''s fuel output is falling after Ukrainian drone strikes on refineries. Seasonal spikes in gasoline and diesel demand could push the system into a deeper crisis, experts say.

Title: Why the Williams sisters and other stars are playing longer
Publication date: 2026-06-17T09:27:00Z
Description: More than three decades after they burst onto the tennis scene, Venus and Serena Williams are still playing at the top level. Why are we seeing elite athletes carrying on into their 40s and beyond?

Title: Bavarian top court rules state spy agency can monitor AfD
Publication date: 2026-06-17T09:17:00Z
Description: Bavaria''s regional domestic intelligence agency can monitor the right-wing populist AfD, the state''s top court has ruled. Several states are trying to implement similar steps, with the opposition party challenging it.

Title: World Cup dreams come true for young German footballers
Publication date: 2026-06-17T08:29:00Z
Description: Three young US college soccer players from Germany have had the opportunity to meet some of their World Cup heroes, as the men''s natonal team''s base camp is just around the corner.

Title: New exhibitions for Anish Kapoor: Art on the edge
Publication date: 2026-06-17T08:13:00Z
Description: His art challenges our perception: Forms vanish and perspectives shift. Anish Kapoor leads the viewer to the edge of the abyss — and sometimes, even beyond. Two new exhibitions revisit his work.

Title: Brazil: Court convicts Bolsonaro''s son over US lobbying
Publication date: 2026-06-17T05:05:00Z
Description: The ex-president''s son Eduardo Bolsonaro has been sentenced to four ⁠years and two months for meddling in his father''s coup attempt trial by seeking help from the US.

Title: G7: Leaders discuss economy, AI security risks
Publication date: 2026-06-17T05:01:00Z
Description: The third and final day of the summit will focus on economic growth and digital security. On a Ukraine-focused Tuesday, Trump said he had a "good" meeting with Zelenskyy. Follow DW for more.

Title: G7 vows new Russia sanctions amid optimism for Ukraine peace
Publication date: 2026-06-17T03:53:00Z
Description: G7 leaders, such as German Chancellor Merz, are sounding more upbeat about the push for peace in Ukraine. The G7 is looking to hit Russia with new energy sanctions as the Strait of Hormuz is expected to reopen.

Title: Russian artist critical of Putin shot dead in Poland
Publication date: 2026-06-16T11:25:00Z
Description: Three days before his killing, Semyon Skrepetsky had protested outside the Russian embassy in Berlin. He held an icon-like caricature of Russian President Vladimir Putin with Soviet leader Josef Stalin.

Title: Germany''s Merz: Who are his international allies?
Publication date: 2026-06-16T11:24:00Z
Description: German Chancellor Friedrich Merz has forged relations with Donald Trump, Emmanuel Macron, Keir Starmer and Giorgia Meloni. With some he is surprisingly close.

Title: Diplomats and abuse — chipping at the shied of immunity
Publication date: 2026-06-16T11:20:00Z
Description: Domestic workers who were mistreated by diplomats are often denied justice due to their abusers enjoying diplomatic immunity. But court rulings in the UK and Switzerland have paved the way for change.

Title: European Parliament approves US trade deal to lower tariffs
Publication date: 2026-06-16T11:09:00Z
Description: The European Parliament has approved cutting tariffs on many US imports to comply with a deal signed last year. US President Trump had given the bloc a July 4 deadline to meet its side of the deal.

Title: Germany news: Population shrinks for first time since COVID-induced dip in 2020
Publication date: 2026-06-16T11:02:00Z
Description: A dip in net migration meant it could not cancel out Germany''s low birth rates in 2025. Meanwhile, fuel prices dip amid news of a possible deal between the US and Iran. And Merz gives Trump a Germany jersey. DW has more.

Title: World Cup: Cape Verde hero and Iran suffer US travel woes
Publication date: 2026-06-16T10:57:00Z
Description: After starring in Cape Verde''s draw with Spain, goalkeeper Vozinha shared his sadness that an expensive travel bond stopped his mother from attending. On the same day, Iran''s coach said his team were being "oppressed."

Title: 5 charged in plot to attack Trump''s UFC event, DOJ says
Publication date: 2026-06-17T01:19:00Z
Description: The alleged plan called for flying explosives-laden drones and shooting panicked crowd members as they fled the event on the White House lawn.

Title: US, Iran, Hezbollah spar over murky terms of ceasefire deal
Publication date: 2026-06-16T23:16:00Z
Description: Iran''s top diplomat has said continued Israeli presence in Lebanon would violate the interim US–Iran deal to end the war. Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu insists Israel will remain as long as necessary.

Title: Germany''s Merz: Who are his international allies?
Publication date: 2026-06-16T18:48:00Z
Description: German Chancellor Friedrich Merz has forged relations with Donald Trump, Emmanuel Macron, Keir Starmer and Giorgia Meloni. With some he is surprisingly close.

Title: Russian ship fires warning shots at British yacht in Channel
Publication date: 2026-06-16T18:47:00Z
Description: Russia''s Defense Ministry fired at a boat that made a "dangerous approach." The incident took place outside of UK territorial waters in the English Channel south of the Isle of Wight.

Title: CRISPR gene-editing for crops: Precision tool or new risk?
Publication date: 2026-06-16T17:44:00Z
Description: The EU is poised to ease restrictions on crops developed using novel genetic techniques. While supporters say the technology could help farmers adapt to climate change, critics argue its effects remain poorly understood.

Title: Why women''s inheritance reform has stalled across Arab world
Publication date: 2026-06-16T16:29:00Z
Description: Sharia-based inheritance laws continue to disadvantage millions of women across the Middle East. What could prompt real change for the next generation of girls?

Title: Failed joint jet project highlights Europe''s defense dilemma
Publication date: 2026-06-16T16:03:00Z
Description: The collapse of a Franco-German fighter jet project and a faltering joint battle tank program show how national industrial interests can outweigh common defense objectives.

Title: Iran''s hardliners fear being sidelined in US deal
Publication date: 2026-06-17T12:36:00Z
Description: As an Iran-US memorandum aimed at ending the war moves closer to formal signature, hardline supporters of the Islamic Republic fear losing influence as Iran''s politics shift from maximalist defiance to compromise.

Title: Poland: Arrest after Russian artist and Putin critic killed
Publication date: 2026-06-18T10:47:00Z
Description: Prime Minister Donald Tusk says Lublin police arrested a suspect in the fatal shooting of the Russian national and critical artist known as Semyon Skrepetsky. He said investigators were still seeking a "mastermind."

Title: NATO: US lashes out, alliance head says everything''s fine
Publication date: 2026-06-18T10:38:00Z
