Place name: Oskarshausen, Address: bei Dresden, Burgker Str. 39, 01705 Freital, Germany, Local type: amusement_park, indoor_playground, playground, go_karting_venue, race_course, amusement_center, event_venue, sports_activity_location, restaurant, food, point_of_interest, establishment Phone number: 0351 79992770 Website: http://www.oskarshausen.de/

Reviews


Rewiew: Fantastic day out, highly recommend for children and families - a lot to do.
Id say our 10 year old is really the upper age limit for the attractions.
The wristband is good value for money.
Lots to explore inside as well, although some of the activities can be a little more on the expensive side.
We found the food good value for money.
We also visited the pumpkin exhibition, also fantastic.
Looking forward to visiting in the Spring.. Review published on: 7 months ago

Rewiew: You can enjoy without entrance fee. When you enter, you are asked to buy free pass for 12€. But most of the attraction needs additional fee and I don’t think free pass is needed. And it is better to bring cash because you use 1 or 2 €for attraction.. Review published on: 2 years ago

Rewiew: Variety of rides, slides, a small kids cinema. Also has lots of cafes.  The ticket and food prices are high though.
There are some hand crafting options for the kids at additional price.. Review published on: 7 months ago

Place name: McDonald''s, Address: Wilsdruffer Str. 19/21, 01067 Dresden-Altstadt, Germany, Local type: fast_food_restaurant, restaurant, food, point_of_interest, establishment Phone number: 0351 4965087 Website: https://www.mcdonalds.com/de/de-de/restaurant-suche.html/l/dresden/wilsdruffer-strasse-19-21/449&cid=listing_0449

Reviews


Rewiew: We ordered our food and we wanted to go to the toilet but even if you are a McDonalds customer you have to pay 0.50 cents to be able to use the restroom. Food was okay like any other restaurant.. Review published on: 8 months ago

Rewiew: I visited in the morning, shorty after opening. The place was almost empty and the food was prepared fairly quickly. Coffee was great.
I haven''t visited the washroom, but I believe it''s paid washroom, as it is the case with all public washrooms in Germany.. Review published on: a year ago

Rewiew: Very big prices but food was good and tasty, you have to pay for toilet.. Review published on: 8 months ago

Place name: BallsportArena Dresden, Address: Weißeritzstr. 4, 01067 Dresden, Germany, Local type: sports_complex, physiotherapist, athletic_field, event_venue, association_or_organization, sports_activity_location, health, restaurant, food, point_of_interest, service, establishment Phone number: 0351 4824940 Website: http://www.ballsportarena-dresden.de/

Reviews


Rewiew: I go there every other week. Very well kept, organized, friendly staff, large areas and good variety of sports are offered.. Review published on: 2 months ago

Rewiew: I watched an amazing handball match Dresden against TUV and dresden won. Amazing drinks and foods and seats but you cant bring own drinks.. Review published on: 2 years ago

Rewiew: Very good experience with the badminton courts here. Well priced for what we get in Dresden and good facilities. 👍🏻

I only wished the badminton courts had softer flooring.. but I guess these are multi utility floors reusable for other sports as well.. Review published on: 3 years ago

Place name: Ristorante "Mamma Mia", Address: Kreuzstraße 1-3, 01067 Dresden, Germany, Local type: italian_restaurant, wine_bar, mediterranean_restaurant, noodle_shop, family_restaurant, vegetarian_restaurant, european_restaurant, bar, restaurant, food, point_of_interest, establishment Phone number: 0351 4976600 Website: https://www.mammamia-dresden.de/

Reviews


Rewiew: Mamma Mia restaurant has a rather cozy decor. We ordered two pasta dishes from the lunch menu. The taste of both pastas was decent, edible, but not exactly outstanding. The accompanying salads were quite ordinary, nothing remarkable. If you''re here for lunch and aren''t too picky about the food, Mamma Mia might be a suitable choice.. Review published on: a month ago

Rewiew: It was a wonderful dining experience. The staff—especially Dino—were very helpful. I think you should definitely try all the dishes without hesitation.. Review published on: a month ago

Rewiew: Great food but very busy. We had to wait for a table to clear up even though we had a reservation and arrived on time. The food, which tasted amazing, took about an hour to arrive. All in all a great restaurant that should cut down on how many tables it has.. Review published on: 2 months ago

Place name: Radisson Blu Park Hotel & Conference Centre, Dresden Radebeul, Address: Nizzastraße 55, 01445 Radebeul, Germany, Local type: hotel, resort_hotel, bar, lodging, restaurant, food, point_of_interest, establishment Phone number: 0351 83210 Website: https://www.radissonhotels.com/en-us/hotels/radisson-blu-conference-dresden-radebeul?cid=a:se+b:gmb+c:emea+i:local+e:rdb+d:cese+h:DEDRSCCR

Reviews


Rewiew: We had a very pleasant family stay (2adults+1yo) in a studio appartment. Very practical, and spacious. Minor disappointment is the lack of a decent cooler for baby milk products and such. Excellent parking space, helpful and friendly service. We used the restaurant in the hotel twice for dinner, which is acceptable but nothing great (due to being a buffet I think). Breakfast is very good. There''s a great indoor swimming pool, which we preferred over the location. The hotel is a bit away from Dresden center.. Review published on: a month ago

Rewiew: The hotel offers a beautiful view and a really great atmosphere. The staff were extremely polite and welcoming, which made the stay even more enjoyable. Parking was also very convenient and well-organised.

On the downside, the breakfast was fairly average, and it was a bit disappointing that room service is not available. Overall, though, a pleasant stay with some strong highlights.. Review published on: 2 months ago

Rewiew: The cleanliness was very good and the staff were very friendly, but it definitely does not meet the standard of a 4-star Radisson Hotel Group hotel. The bed was not comfortable and the pillows were not good at all. There are no power outlets next to the bed; the only outlet is across the room near the TV. Since it is an older hotel, bedside outlets were apparently never installed. The walls are extremely thin, so you can easily hear noise from outside and other rooms. Parking is available, but it costs €16 per day, and there was no clear information about this beforehand.. Review published on: a month ago

Place name: Kutscherschänke, Address: Münzgasse 10, 01067 Dresden-Altstadt, Germany, Local type: german_restaurant, european_restaurant, restaurant, food, point_of_interest, establishment Phone number: 0351 4965123 Website: https://www.kutscherschaenke-dresden.de/

Reviews


Rewiew: A Rustic Gem in the Heart of Dresden!

If you’re looking for authentic, hearty Saxon comfort food, **Kutscherschänke** is an absolute must-visit. Nestled right in the historic Old Town near the Frauenkirche, the rustic, wood-paneled atmosphere makes you feel like you''ve stepped back in time.

I started with the **dumpling soup**, which was the perfect warm-up—flavorful, savory, and clearly made with care. For the main course, the **beef ribs** were the star of the show. They were incredibly tender, rich, and exactly the kind of "stick-to-your-ribs" meal you want after a day of exploring the city.

What really set the experience apart, though, was the **service**. Despite the restaurant being quite lively, the staff was attentive, welcoming, and remarkably fast. They made me feel right at home from the moment I walked in.

Highly recommended for anyone wanting a true taste of Dresden with top-notch hospitality!. Review published on: 2 months ago

Rewiew: Authentic swiss atmosphere and food. The food tasted great and the beet was excellent. The service was fast and the staff were friendly. The decorations of the place are pretty unique. I’d recommend the schnitzel.. Review published on: 3 months ago

Rewiew: What great authentic German food and vibe. I visited during December and the Christmas markets. It was very busy and many people left without getting in, but luckily I made a reservation in advance. The server was kind and fun and offered a great meal. And definitely get the apple strudel!. Review published on: 6 months ago

Place name: Schwerelos - Das Achterbahnrestaurant, Address: Wr. Pl. 10, 01069 Dresden, Germany, Local type: german_restaurant, tourist_attraction, family_restaurant, european_restaurant, restaurant, food, point_of_interest, establishment Phone number: 0351 82127900 Website: https://rollercoaster-dresden.de/

Reviews


Rewiew: We had a lot of fun here during a quick stop before our train, really bizarre and funny experience to watch the food arrive by rollercoaster. We had great service from Ali, who understood that we didn''t have much time. The food arrived quickly and was very tasty.. Review published on: 3 weeks ago

Rewiew: Super cool place to have a family branch. Friendly to the kids, there''s a cute kids playmat with toys here.
Food is being served through fun railways of different paths. Super cute Kitty robot brings drinks and takes away the dishes, can also sing you a "Happy birthday" song.🎂
Wanna say special thanks to our waiters Ulli and Ali.🤗🥰 We had lots of fun.😋
My daughter won a special Gift card for our next visit. We will definitely come back more than once.. Review published on: 3 months ago

Rewiew: The service was great, very kind and always checking on us. The food tasted good as well but I cant give more than 2 stars because it is wayy to expensive for what you are getting. It''s a cool experience for one time but I wouldn''t go here another time. Review published on: 3 weeks ago

Place name: Campingplatz Dresden-Mockritz, Address: Boderitzer Str. 30, 01217 Dresden-Plauen, Germany, Local type: campground, lodging, sports_activity_location, restaurant, food, point_of_interest, service, establishment Phone number: 0351 4715250 Website: https://www.cbm-camping.de/dresden/

Reviews


Rewiew: Nice and comfortable place. Showers were coin operated, however time and water pressure was great as well as privacy. Staff was super nice and very professional, good english. I can recommend this place for anyone visiting Dresden, you will not be disappointed.. Review published on: 9 months ago

Rewiew: Nice and professional staff, newly renovated, clean and well maintained bath- and service rooms. Bus access right outside the camping site, busses every 20 min. to beautiful Dresden. All in all a great site to stay over night or a few days.. Review published on: 11 months ago

Rewiew: Very nice and quiet camping, extraordinary service from owner Mandy. Very helpful and pleasant! Bus stop in front of camping with good connection to city center. I strongly recommend!
Warm greetings to Mandy!. Review published on: 9 months ago

Place name: Ballhaus Watzke, Address: Kötzschenbroder Str. 1, 01139 Dresden-Pieschen, Germany, Local type: brewpub, brewery, concert_hall, banquet_hall, beer_garden, auditorium, live_music_venue, wedding_venue, event_venue, pub, bar, restaurant, food, manufacturer, point_of_interest, service, establishment Phone number: 0351 852920 Website: http://www.watzke.de/

Reviews


Rewiew: The best (!) beer in Dresden (from the brewery Watzke) in their (out of the three) biggest and probably oldest brewery with a beer garden, views of the old town and great, traditional German food to go along with the beer. When in Dresden, this is a must!. Review published on: 7 months ago

Rewiew: perfect place to go during spring. lovely biergarten restaurant at dresden and you get perfect view of sunset by the river.  found my most favourite German cuisine steak au four!

all the beers are fresh and good.. Review published on: a year ago

Rewiew: An interesting experience, we originally planned to go to Burger King, and since the parking lot we found was next to it, we assumed it belonged to Burger King. However, after parking, we realized we couldn’t exit, only to find out that the parking actually belonged to Ballhaus Watzke.

I went inside and explained that we had mistakenly parked there, asking if they could open the gate so we could leave. I even mentioned that it was an honest mistake, but they insisted that we had to pay €5 to exit. The only way to avoid the fee was to place an order at their restaurant.

I rated this place 2 stars due to the parking issue. They should have allowed us to leave, as most parking areas do, without charging a fee for a brief mistake. I wish I had discovered this restaurant under different circumstances, rather than feeling forced into dining there.

Additionally, the staff was not friendly, no smiles, no extra effort to guide us, especially since I don’t have much experience with German food. A little hospitality would have made the experience much better.. Review published on: a year ago

Place name: McDonald''s, Address: Peschelstraße 38, 01139 Dresden, Germany, Local type: fast_food_restaurant, restaurant, food, point_of_interest, establishment Phone number: 0351 8588422 Website: https://www.mcdonalds.com/de/de-de/restaurant-suche.html/l/dresden/peschelstrasse-38/757&cid=listing_0757

Reviews


Rewiew: We were disappointed of the place🥲 French fries was raw, meat was a bit burnt. The toilet isn’t comfortable at all.. Review published on: in the last week

Rewiew: Damn, this place is kind of a nightmare if you have kids. Was expecting an indoor playpen since it’s shown in the pics, but no, looks like that’s not the case. And I had to wait over 30 mins with kids…I was just about to request a refund when my food was brought. The order was completely messed up.

I just ate what they gave and left. Not worth my time and energy, won’t be back here again. Also the staff seemed oddly incompetent…like the whole place just seemed a bit off.. Review published on: a year ago

Rewiew: Arrived later in the evening, and despite only having a few customers, the tables were not wiped clean. Entry is bad it''s right in front of the drive thru.  Ketchup was spilling out of my burger and smeared on top of the bun. Overall...it''s a McDonald''s.. Review published on: 3 years ago');


